<h1 class="text-2xl font-bold text-zinc-100 mb-6">Using Templates</h1>

<p class="text-zinc-400 mb-6">
  Templates are pre-built configurations that set up your
  <code class="text-zinc-300 bg-zinc-800 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-sm">.botster/</code> directory
  for common workflows. Browse and install them from the hub settings page.
</p>

<h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-zinc-200 mt-8 mb-3">Installing templates</h2>
<ol class="list-decimal list-inside text-zinc-400 space-y-2 mb-6">
  <li>Open your hub in the browser</li>
  <li>Go to <span class="text-zinc-300 font-medium">Settings</span></li>
  <li>Switch to the <span class="text-zinc-300 font-medium">Templates</span> tab</li>
  <li>Browse available templates and click <span class="text-zinc-300 font-medium">Install</span></li>
</ol>

<h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-zinc-200 mt-8 mb-3">Scope</h2>
<p class="text-zinc-400 mb-4">
  Templates can be installed at two scopes:
</p>
<ul class="list-disc list-inside text-zinc-400 space-y-1 mb-6">
  <li><span class="text-zinc-300 font-medium">Repository</span> &mdash; written to <code class="text-zinc-300 bg-zinc-800 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-sm">{repo}/.botster/</code>, committed with your code</li>
  <li><span class="text-zinc-300 font-medium">Device</span> &mdash; written to <code class="text-zinc-300 bg-zinc-800 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-sm">~/.botster/</code>, applies to all repos</li>
</ul>

<h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-zinc-200 mt-8 mb-3">Uninstalling</h2>
<p class="text-zinc-400">
  Uninstall from the same Templates tab. This removes the files that the template created.
</p>
